Develop a PHP script that generates a random password consisting of a combination of
letters, numbers, and special characters.

CODE:
<?php
function generatePassword($length = 12) {
    // Characters to use in the password
    $characters = 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789!@#$%^&*()_+=-[]{}<>?';
    
    $password = '';
    $maxIndex = strlen($characters) - 1;

    // Loop to pick random characters
    for ($i = 0; $i < $length; $i++) {
        $password .= $characters[rand(0, $maxIndex)];
    }

    return $password;
}

// Generate and display a password of length 12
echo "Generated Password: " . generatePassword(12);
?>
